-- Interior Chief Says Drought May Cause Record Wildfires in U.S.
-- B y   M a r k   D r a j e m
-- 2013-07-17T14:19:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-17/interior-chief-says-drought-may-cause-record-wildfires-in-u-s-.html
U.S. Interior Secretary Sally Jewell
said that there may be a record season for wildfires this year
as severe drought conditions persist in the West.  Jewell, in her first testimony to the House Natural
Resources committee, said a decade of drought has led to an
accumulation of “hazardous fuels in our forests and
rangelands.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Drajem in  Washington  at 
 mdrajem@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
